cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with analyzing online communication networks and detecting temporal events within them. This falls under the scope of social and information networks.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses constructing a model for detecting temporal events in online communication data. This involves designing and implementing algorithms, which falls under the scope of software engineering.
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with analyzing and discovering meaningful patterns in online communication data. This involves information retrieval techniques such as text mining and topic modeling.
4. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) - The paper deals with analyzing social networks and online communication data to understand human behavior and interactions. This falls under the scope of computational social science.
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper involves natural language processing techniques such as text mining and topic modeling to analyze online communication data. This falls under the scope of computation and language.
